</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FAA6563E94FED7E40FFFD15CACB7045" pageId="39" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="470F36E8E94FED7E40FFFD15CACB7045" blockId="39.[120,649,226,1077]" pageId="39" pageNumber="39">COMMENTS: The unique specimen is not very well preserved, much of the cuticle of the body crumpled and softened, making sutures and small sclerites difficult to observe (e.g., proscutellum, tergite 1, metaspiracular area). However, the right wing is very well preserved (the left wing is distorted); the proboscis is cleared, distended, and most of the mouthparts are separated (fig. 12A), allowing observation of fine details of these structures.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
